  "prompt": "What do you do if you like someone?",
  "response": "Here are some healthy approaches if you like someone:\n\n1. Get to know them better\n\u2022 Spend time together\n\u2022 Have conversations\n\u2022 Show genuine interest in their life\n\n2. Be yourself\n\u2022 Don't try to be someone you're not\n\u2022 Be authentic and genuine\n\u2022 Let them see your true personality\n\n3. Show interest\n\u2022 Smile and be friendly\n\u2022 Ask them questions about themselves\n\u2022 Pay attention when they speak\n\u2022 Look for opportunities to spend time together\n\n4. Communicate\n\u2022 If comfortable, express your feelings\n\u2022 Be clear but respectful\n\u2022 Be prepared for any response\n\u2022 Don't pressure them\n\n5. Be respectful\n\u2022 Respect their feelings and boundaries\n\u2022 Accept their response graciously\n\u2022 Don't take rejection personally\n\n6. Build a connection\n\u2022 Find common interests\n\u2022 Share experiences\n\u2022 Show that you care about them as a person\n\n7. Consider your approach\n\u2022 If it's a friend, be careful not to risk the friendship\n\u2022 If it's someone you don't know well, take time to build a connection\n\nRemember, every situation is unique, and there's no guaranteed method. The most important things are respect, honesty, and being genuine.",
